# UTextarea in app forms

Use Nuxt UI `UTextarea` for multi-line text inside forms. Do not use native `<textarea>`.

## Pattern

- Keep `UFormField` + `v-model` on the field model.
- Add `class="w-full"` like other catalog inputs.
- Set `:rows` when the field should not use the default height of `3`.
- Do not add manual border, background, or padding classes that duplicate Nuxt UI styling.

```vue
<!-- BAD -->
<UFormField label="Notas" name="notes">
  <textarea
    v-model="state.notes"
    class="w-full min-h-24 rounded-lg border border-default px-3 py-2 text-sm bg-default"
    rows="4"
  />
</UFormField>

<!-- GOOD -->
<UFormField label="Notas" name="notes">
  <UTextarea v-model="state.notes" class="w-full" :rows="4" />
</UFormField>
```
